'I've always been pretty trim but recently I've been training hard at the gym and only eating one or two big meals in the evenings.

'I was still surprised I managed to eat it all - my mates can't believe it.'

James, from Hadleigh, Essex, added that he was feeling very unwell when he finally finished the meal on Saturday.

He said: 'By the end it gets quite hard to stomach each mouthful without feeling sick.

'I think the owner could see I was flagging so he started playing "Eye of the Tiger" through the restaurant speakers to keep me going.

'It really did the trick and helped me get through the wall and complete it.'

Restaurant owner Will Fishenden said they had been offering the sandwich challenge for over a year - but no one had completed it before.

'It came about from my love of Man vs Food and we thought we needed to produce our own challenge,' he said.

'I was amazed when James managed to finish it all as we have had a lot of much bigger guys than him come in and fail.

'We have had 117 attempts and only one success - James is truly a lean, mean, eating machine.'

The sandwich has now been given an extra layer as the eating challenge is taken to the next level.

